snippet.textDisplay:
I made the switch from PlayStation to Xbox with the 360 and never went back. I had a PS3 for a month but then sold it on eBay. I love Xbox’s online gaming and achievement system (has added a lot of replay value to games I would’ve otherwise stopped playing... trophy system was a silly ripoff in my humble opinion). Xbox One X definitely stumbled, but GamePass is much better than anything Sony had to offer, and I got to play Resident Evil 2 which was the most important game of this generation for me.

I have great memories of PSOne and PS2, but I just don’t care about owning a PlayStation console anymore. I believe a lot of PlayStation fanboys hate on Xbox without actually ever having even played one.
snippet.textOriginal:
I made the switch from PlayStation to Xbox with the 360 and never went back. I had a PS3 for a month but then sold it on eBay. I love Xbox’s online gaming and achievement system (has added a lot of replay value to games I would’ve otherwise stopped playing...  trophy system was a silly ripoff in my humble opinion). Xbox One X definitely stumbled, but GamePass is much better than anything Sony had to offer, and I got to play Resident Evil 2 which was the most important game of this generation for me. 

I have great memories of PSOne and PS2, but I just don’t care about owning a PlayStation console anymore. I believe a lot of PlayStation fanboys hate on Xbox without actually ever having even played one.
